&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Cyber espionage up, but basic defences still down, DBIR shows&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cyber espionage is the most interesting aspect of the data relating to real data breaches that we are seeing because it is becoming more prevalent &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.computerweekly.com/news/450417570/Cyber-espionage-up-but-basic-defences-still-down-DBIR-shows&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.computerweekly.com/news/450417570/Cyber-espionage-up-but-basic-defences-still-down-DBIR-shows&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Verizon 2017 Data Breach Investigations Report&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1,935 confirmed data breaches. That means you get a detailed insight into &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.verizonenterprise.com/verizon-insights-lab/dbir/2017/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.verizonenterprise.com/verizon-insights-lab/dbir/2017/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;1.1 Billion Identities Leaked Via Data Breaches in 2016; Email Is The&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Trak.in (blog) In total, there were 1209 data breaches across the world, which resulted in the exposure of these 1.1 billion identities. Interestingly, while the number &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://trak.in/tags/business/2017/04/27/1-1b-identities-leaked-data-breach-email/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://trak.in/tags/business/2017/04/27/1-1b-identities-leaked-data-breach-email/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;How can CIOs best secure the future of their company data?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;hellip; warnings from cyber security experts, who expressed their concern that come 2017, businesses will be subject to a significant rise in data breaches, &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.thecsuite.co.uk/cio/security-cio/how-can-cios-best-secure-the-future-of-their-company-data/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.thecsuite.co.uk/cio/security-cio/how-can-cios-best-secure-the-future-of-their-company-data/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Hackers plead guilty to 2015 TalkTalk data breach&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Despite this victory, data breaches are constantly happening, and the threat is gaining momentum. A recent example of a significant breach was the &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.cbronline.com/news/cybersecurity/business/hackers-plead-guilty-2015-talktalk-data-breach/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.cbronline.com/news/cybersecurity/business/hackers-plead-guilty-2015-talktalk-data-breach/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;1.1 bn identities exposed in data breaches in 2016: Symantec&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;New Delhi, Apr 26 (PTI) Nearly 1.1 billion identities were exposed by cyber criminals in data breaches across the globe last year, almost double &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/1.1-bn-identities-exposed-in-data-breaches-in-2016-symantec/1/939112.html&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/1.1-bn-identities-exposed-in-data-breaches-in-2016-symantec/1/939112.html&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;P2PE&amp;rsquo;s Silver Lining In Cybercrime&amp;rsquo;s Dark Cloud&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Data breaches are not exactly news  since the Target breach of 2013, they&amp;rsquo;ve gone from being something that was little considered outside a fairly &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.pymnts.com/news/security-and-risk/2017/finding-the-p2pe-silver-lining-in-the-dark-cloud-of-expanding-cybercrime-bluefin-technology/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.pymnts.com/news/security-and-risk/2017/finding-the-p2pe-silver-lining-in-the-dark-cloud-of-expanding-cybercrime-bluefin-technology/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Thales: 34% of U.S. Federal Government Agencies Experienced Data Breach in&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Yahoo Finance When it comes to data breaches, 34 percent of federal respondents experienced a data breach in the last year and 65 percent experienced a data &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://finance.yahoo.com/news/thales-34-u-federal-government-120000601.html&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://finance.yahoo.com/news/thales-34-u-federal-government-120000601.html&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s Just Plain Risky Not to Do A Risk Analysis: Recent OCR Settlement One&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;JD Supra (press release) Data breaches in the health care sector are ubiquitous; for example, a report from analytics company Protenus, Inc. indicates that at least one health &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.jdsupra.com/legalnews/it-s-just-plain-risky-not-to-do-a-risk-90212/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.jdsupra.com/legalnews/it-s-just-plain-risky-not-to-do-a-risk-90212/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;ITRC: 2017 Data Breaches on Record Pace&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(ITRC) is this blog&amp;rsquo;s go-to source for current breach statistics.  &lt;a href=&#34;https://blog.varonis.com/itrc-2017-breaches-on-record-pace/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;https://blog.varonis.com/itrc-2017-breaches-on-record-pace/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;34 percent of US government agencies have had data breaches in the last&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BetaNews According to a new report from systems security specialist Thales e-Security and 451 Research, US federal agencies are facing threats caused by &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;https://betanews.com/2017/04/27/us-government-data-breach/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;https://betanews.com/2017/04/27/us-government-data-breach/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Securing Your Data From Internal Threats&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Data breaches are an increasingly common affair. A recent government report showed that 46% of all businesses identified at least one cyber attack in &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/securing-your-data-from-internal-threats_us_5901f245e4b00acb75f1852c&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/securing-your-data-from-internal-threats_us_5901f245e4b00acb75f1852c&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;cyber espionage and ransomware attacks are on the increase - Verizon&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ransomware use has exploded recently as an easy way for cyber criminals to make money. As long as people keep on paying the ransoms, &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.information-age.com/cyber-espionage-ransomware-attacks-increase-verizon-123465968/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.information-age.com/cyber-espionage-ransomware-attacks-increase-verizon-123465968/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Verizon Data Breach Investigations Report Reveals Ransomware&amp;hellip;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;hellip; reported last year that the 2016 DBIR report was based on an analysis of 100,000 security incidents of which 2,260 were confirmed data breaches.  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.eweek.com/security/verizon-data-breach-investigations-report-reveals-ransomware-surge&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.eweek.com/security/verizon-data-breach-investigations-report-reveals-ransomware-surge&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Data Breaches Top 500 to Date in 2017&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The latest count from the Identity Theft Resource Center (ITRC) reports that there have been 516 data breaches recorded this year through April 25 &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://247wallst.com/technology-3/2017/04/27/data-breaches-top-500-to-date-in-2017/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://247wallst.com/technology-3/2017/04/27/data-breaches-top-500-to-date-in-2017/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Stolen, Unencrypted Drive Causes Data Security Concern for 15K&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recent potential healthcare data breaches include a stolen unencrypted jump drive, a large-scale fraud scheme, and a ransomware attack.  &lt;a href=&#34;http://healthitsecurity.com/news/stolen-unencrypted-drive-causes-data-security-concern-for-15k&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://healthitsecurity.com/news/stolen-unencrypted-drive-causes-data-security-concern-for-15k&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Chipotle PoS Part of Rising Data Breach Problem for Retail Industry&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I don&amp;rsquo;t often write about individual data breaches, but when I read a comment in eSecurity Planet that point-of-sale (PoS) breaches are increasing &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.itbusinessedge.com/blogs/data-security/chipotle-pos-part-of-rising-data-breach-problem-for-retail-industry.html&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.itbusinessedge.com/blogs/data-security/chipotle-pos-part-of-rising-data-breach-problem-for-retail-industry.html&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;New study finds teaching hospitals at higher risk of data breaches&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A new study of HHS statistics on data breaches reported from late 2009 through 2016 published by JAMA Internal Medicine provides new insight into &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.scrypt.com/blog/new-study-finds-teaching-hospitals-higher-risk-data-breaches-occurring/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;https://www.scrypt.com/blog/new-study-finds-teaching-hospitals-higher-risk-data-breaches-occurring/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;So You&amp;rsquo;ve Been Hacked: The Changing Landscape of Post-Data Breach Liability&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The impact of serious data breaches are becoming both more common and more costly for businesses with each major attack. According to the New &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.newyorklawjournal.com/id=1202784725267/So-Youve-Been-Hacked-The-Changing-Landscape-of-PostData-Breach-Liability&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.newyorklawjournal.com/id=1202784725267/So-Youve-Been-Hacked-The-Changing-Landscape-of-PostData-Breach-Liability&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Sophos Endpoint Update and UTM 9.4 IPS&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;occurring the following IPS alert began popping. Intrusion Prevention Alert.  &lt;a href=&#34;https://community.sophos.com/products/unified-threat-management/f/endpoint-protection-antivirus-and-device-control/91344/sophos-endpoint-update-and-utm-9-4-ips&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;https://community.sophos.com/products/unified-threat-management/f/endpoint-protection-antivirus-and-device-control/91344/sophos-endpoint-update-and-utm-9-4-ips&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Annual Verizon security report says sloppiness causes most data breaches&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;More than half (51 percent) of the data breaches analyzed in the report involved malware, 73 percent of the breaches were financially motivated, and &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.infoworld.com/article/3193028/security/annual-verizon-security-report-says-sloppiness-causes-most-data-breaches.html&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.infoworld.com/article/3193028/security/annual-verizon-security-report-says-sloppiness-causes-most-data-breaches.html&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Titan IC sets sail to secure the world&amp;rsquo;s major cloud providers&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This solution accelerates Deep Packet Inspection (DPI) and Security Information &amp;amp; Event Management (SIEM) systems by allowing thousands of cyber &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.design-reuse.com/news/41894/titan-ic-helios-f1-fpga-regex-processor-aws-f1-amazon-machine-instance.html&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;https://www.design-reuse.com/news/41894/titan-ic-helios-f1-fpga-regex-processor-aws-f1-amazon-machine-instance.html&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Sophos Central Management / XG-210 / WAPS / Endpoint Protection?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Endpoint Protection clients and any Sophos WAPS all in one console &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;https://community.sophos.com/products/xg-firewall/f/firewall-and-policies/91331/sophos-central-management-xg-210-waps-endpoint-protection/330913&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;https://community.sophos.com/products/xg-firewall/f/firewall-and-policies/91331/sophos-central-management-xg-210-waps-endpoint-protection/330913&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Verizon data breach study finds cyber espionage on the rise&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The top three three industries targeted by data breaches were financial services, healthcare and the public sector, representing 25 percent, 15 percent &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://thehill.com/policy/cybersecurity/330980-verizon-data-breach-study-finds-cyber-espionage-on-the-rise&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://thehill.com/policy/cybersecurity/330980-verizon-data-breach-study-finds-cyber-espionage-on-the-rise&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt; From raw data to actionable intelligence: The art and science of endpoint&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SecurityBrief Asia Many companies offer solutions for endpoint protection, whether that endpoint is physical or virtual, mobile or in a data centre or in the cloud.  &lt;a href=&#34;https://securitybrief.asia/story/raw-data-actionable-intelligence-art-and-science-endpoint-security/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;https://securitybrief.asia/story/raw-data-actionable-intelligence-art-and-science-endpoint-security/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Verizon DBIR Shows Attack Patterns Vary Widely By Industry&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Data that Verizon collected from security incidents and data breaches that it investigated in 2016 showed, for instance, that financial and insurance &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.darkreading.com/attacks-breaches/verizon-dbir-shows-attack-patterns-vary-widely-by-industry/d/d-id/1328757&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.darkreading.com/attacks-breaches/verizon-dbir-shows-attack-patterns-vary-widely-by-industry/d/d-id/1328757&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
